<H3>Instruction</FONT> of the BodyImage</H3>
<FONT FACE="Osaka"><P>Before starting the measurement, you have to set the fields listed below in the Setting Options window.</P>
<B><P>[ID :]</B> Subject name or subject ID. This field can be blank.</P>

<B><P>[Image File: ]</B> Showing the file name of the image file selected. Click 'Select' to change the picture. Macintosh version of this software can handle natively an image file in PICT and JPEG format(requires QuickTime). Windows version of this software can handle BMP and JPEG format (requires QuickTime for Windows).</P>

<B><P>[Image Distortion Rate]</B> This field specifies the distortion rate of the picture in decimal. 'from 2.0 to 1.8' means that the width of the image file is enlarged in the range of 2.0 times to 1.8 times of the original proportion.</P>

<B><P>[Sequence]</B> This field specifies the display sequence order. 'L-S' means the program displays enlarged picture first, then reduced picture follows, 'S-L' means reduced picture first, then enlarged. You can make the sequence order 'Random' or specify by the external file. Format of the external file is made up of the procedure number (1 for L procedure and 2 for S procedure) and the distortion rate. Each data should be delimited by ",". When the distortion rate is not contained in the file, the distortion rate is set as specified in the "Image Distortion Rate" field.</P>

<B><P>[BGColor]</B> You can change the background color of the main window.
<B><P>[Save data to: ]</B> Location of the data file. You have to select or create new data file before starting the measurement. When you select the file already exists, the program appends the new data at the bottom of the file. First line of the record contains Subject ID and date of the measurement. The measurement data in each trial are from the second line of the record. The record contains the number of trial, displayed distortion rate, and the participant√ïs response data. The response data are calculated as (modified picture width) / (original picture width).</P>
<P>When you finish the setting of necessary option, click 'start' to start the measurement.</P>
